            id: 117954949,
            iid: 1745,
            project_id: 10174980,
            title: 'Changins sword stance ability in one stance modifies the other',
            description:
                "\u003c!---\nPlease read this!\n\nBefore opening a new issue, make sure to search for keywords in the issues\nfiltered by the \"crash\" or \"bug\" label:\n\n- https://gitlab.com/veloren/veloren/-/issues?label_name%5B%5D=type%3A%3Acrash\n- https://gitlab.com/veloren/veloren/-/issues?label_name%5B%5D=type%3A%3Abug\n\nand verify the issue you're about to submit isn't a duplicate.\n---\u003e\n\n### Summary\n\nWhen updating the 'Sword Stance Ability' slots with specific skills from the stance's tree it will modify skills set for that slot in another stance.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open diary.\n2. Fill in the hotbar as follows:\n`[1: sword stance ability][2: sword stance ability][3: stance A][4: stance B][5: stance C]`\n3. Draw sword and change to stance A and place 1st and 2nd skill from the list to slot 1-2.\n  e.g.: `[1: Offensive finisher][2: Offensive Advance]`\n4. Swap to stance B and place 2nd and 3rd skill to slot 1-2.\n  e.g.: `[1: Riposte][2: Parry]`\n5. Swap back to stance A, observes slot 1-2 being reassigned to 2nd and 3rd skill of stance A.\n  e.g.: `[1: Offensive Advance][2: **nothing**]`\n\n### Relevant logs and/or screenshots\n\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003eLogs and/or screenshots of the issue\u003c/summary\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\n\n(Paste any relevant logs - please use code blocks (```) to format console output,\nlogs, and code as it's tough to read otherwise.)\n\n\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003c/details\u003e\n\n#### System details\n\nLinux, OpenSuse Tumbleweed (6.0.3-1-default)\n\n#### Veloren version\n\nPre-Alpha-2022-10-28 (dd62b99)",
